{
  "stem": "13079.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was a bigger camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In Flossenburg, there were 45 accused.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in Buchenwald, 31.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So the purpose was to obtain a judicial determination of the criminality of this operation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the basis for that, the reason for that, was that we had over 3,500 alleged war criminals in the War Crimes cage there at Dachau.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Well, you couldn't give a full-dressed hearing, as was given in the trial of the cases-- camp cases, proper, which we call the mother case-- to each one of these individuals.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We'd still be trying those cases at this time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So what the plan was, and it was considered to be fair, was to get the-- a judicial determination of the criminality of the operation and then use that record of trial presented to subsequent tribunals, in which they would then accept as established the criminality of the operation.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the accused would be those persons who had served there and had participated in the furthering of the common design that was present.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And in that way, they could cut down on the length of time for the trial.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The accused was not presumed to be guilty, but he had the burden of going forward with proof to acquit himself when it was shown that he was there participating in the operation of the camp.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You have put your finger on it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were really on the basis of-- of being representatives of the operations that had occurred.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in that way, we were able to get a cross-section of-- of a proper picture of what transpired in each of these camps.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] we had problems.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One man over here, he only killed 10 people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Another accused over here, he killed 110.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
